You can share macros with users, public groups, and more. The way you share macros is different between Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.

In Salesforce Classic, you can share individual macros.
In Lightning Experience, share macros using folders.

You can change your org-wide default sharing setting for macros or limit access by creating sharing rules to specify which groups of users have access to macros.

Share a folder of macros with other users in Lightning Experience.
Share an individual macro record in Salesforce Classic with other users or groups.
